OL,3,CHeathrow Airport fire: What went wrong?
OL,5,FAccording to Dr Paul Cuffe from the
OL,6,FSchool of Electrical and Electronic
OL,7,FEngineering at University College
OL,8,FDublin: "I would anticipate that a
OL,9,Fmajor airport like Heathrow would have
OL,10,Fsome on-site emergency capability to
OL,11,Fride through a grid disturbance; I
OL,12,Fwould hope that the traffic control
OL,13,Ftower and runway lights weren't
OL,14,Ftotally plunged into darkness.
OL,16,F"However, processing planeloads of
OL,17,Fpassengers requires Heathrow in its
OL,18,Ftotality to consume a town's worth of
OL,19,Felectricity, and the inability to meet
OL,20,Fthis requirement is likely why flights
OL,21,Fhad to be cancelled."
